`SafeAreaEdges="None"` only tells the page layout not to add safe-area padding. You still need two things:

**1. Set `IgnoreSafeArea="True"` on the view itself** so it can extend behind system bars:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             SafeAreaEdges="None">
    <Image Source="photo.jpg"
           Aspect="AspectFill"
           IgnoreSafeArea="True" />
</ContentPage>
```

**2. On Android, opt into edge-to-edge rendering.** The window must draw behind system bars. In your `MainActivity.cs` or a handler:

```csharp
// In Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    if (Window != null)
    {
        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);
        Window.SetStatusBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);
        Window.SetNavigationBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);
    }
}
```

> **Note:** On Android 15+ (API 35), edge-to-edge is enforced by default, so `SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(false)` is already the behavior. For older APIs you must set it explicitly.

On **iOS**, `IgnoreSafeArea="True"` alone should be sufficient — no extra platform code needed.
